{{DISPLAYTITLE:''Vaṭeśvara-siddhānta''}}
'''Vaṭeśvara-siddhānta''' is a [[mathematical]] and [[astronomical]] treatise by [[Vaṭeśvara]] in [[India]] in 904.  This treatise contains fifteen chapters on [[astronomy]] and [[applied mathematics]].

[[Mathematical exercise]]s are included for students to show their comprehension of the text.<ref>[[K. V. Sarma]] (1997), "Vatesvara", [[Encyclopaedia of the History of Science, Technology, and Medicine in Non-Western Cultures]] edited by [[Helaine Selin]], Springer, {{ISBN|978-0-7923-4066-9 }}</ref>

